-- Banco do Brasil Looks at Acquisitions in Chile, Peru, Valor Says
-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 2012-07-09T12:15:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/banco-do-brasil-looks-at-acquisitions-in-chile-peru-valor-says.html
Banco do Brasil SA (BBAS3)  is looking for
acquisitions in Colombia, Peru, Uruguay and Chile as it seeks to
expand its retail banking outside Brazil, newspaper  Valor
Economico  reported, citing international business head Paulo Caffarelli.  Banco do Brasil is already in talks to buy banks in the
four South American countries, Caffarelli said, according to the
Sao Paulo-based newspaper. The bank also plans to expand its
U.S. operations to 20 agencies nationwide from the current
three, Caffarelli told Valor.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in  Rio de Janeiro  at 
